<br>
It is good that VI have recognized that BO4 and muzzle were a pointless proposition, but i do wonder about lower level mages as the haste for the pet is now determined by the masters level.<br>
<br>
Sammerkand <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uyawgmothmage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yawgmothmage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(9/4/02 9:04:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=662.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Two possibilities</span><hr size=1> What they are saying is that all our spells with haste components now work. So if we can give it that much haste, theoritically, it will have that much. However, we won't know for sure unless someone does some testing. Anyone do any testing before servers went down again? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulornicstormfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lornic Stormfury</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(9/4/02 9:58:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=662.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Pet Haste Cap - Comments from 04-09-2002 Patch.</span><hr size=1> Well from the comment they made:<br>
